    "The features are then fed into fully connected layers for classification (Fig. 4) (LeCun et al. 2015; Cong and Zhou 2023).",
    "GANs consist of two neural networks, the generator and the discriminator.",
    "The first takes data from the latent space and generates a new image.",
    "The second takes the generated image and the real image and decides whether the image is authentic or generated by the generator.",
    "Both networks are trained against each other, and in order to obtain a generator that provides images that the discriminator perceives as authentic (Goodfellow et al. 2016; Aggarwal et al. 2021; Vint et al. 2021)."
